commitResults.messageTitle: Fix test consistency: Update TypicalPersons.java to match JSON data

commitResults.messageBody:
Added a new filter command that allows users to search for persons by
their attributes (e.g. subject=math or age=19). This feature integrates
into the existing command system and follows the same design pattern as
find and tag.

New and modified files:
* AttributeContainsPredicate.java — core filtering logic that checks
  whether a person matches the specified attribute criteria.
* FilterCommand.java — executes the filter and updates the displayed list.
* FilterCommandParser.java — parses user input into filter criteria.
* AddressBookParser.java — added “filter” command handling to switch logic.
* PersonBuilder.java — extended to support test data creation with attributes.
* JsonAdaptedPersonTest.java — updated constructor calls to include attributes.

Enhancements:
* Supports multiple attributes and multiple values per attribute.
* Case-insensitive matching and age validation.
* Robust error handling for invalid formats.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add unit tests for attribute-based filtering feature
commitResults.messageBody:
Added comprehensive test coverage to ensure the correctness of the new
filter command and predicate logic.

New test files:
* FilterCommandTest.java — verifies correct filtering behavior with
  various criteria and edge cases.
* AttributeContainsPredicateTest.java — tests the core predicate logic
  for matching and non-matching attributes.
* FilterCommandParserTest.java — validates command parsing, format errors,
  and multiple attribute handling.

These tests confirm that the filter feature behaves consistently and
integrates smoothly with existing commands.

commitResults.messageTitle: Integrate attribute model into Person and parser components
commitResults.messageBody:
Added attribute functionality to enhance person data representation and
support filtering by custom attributes.

Changes:
* Attribute.java — Implement Attribute class representing key–value pairs.
* AttributeContainsPredicate.java — Add predicate for attribute-based matching.
* JsonAdaptedAttribute.java — Support JSON serialization/deserialization of attributes.
* Person.java — Extend Person to include LessonList and Attribute sets.
* SampleDataUtil.java — Populate sample data with attributes for testing.
* CliSyntax.java — Define PREFIX_ATTRIBUTE for attribute-related command parsing.
* AddCommandParser.java — Handle parsing of attributes during person creation.
* MarkCommand.java, RemarkCommand.java, ScheduleCommand.java — Minor updates for integration.

Result:
* Person objects now support attributes in both model and storage layers.
* Commands and parsers are compatible with the new attribute system.
* Enables filter and future attribute-based commands.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update EditCommand and PersonTest for attribute integration
commitResults.messageBody:
Modified:
* EditCommand.java — Updated edit functionality to support editing of
  attribute fields in Person objects.
* PersonTest.java — Added and updated test cases to verify attribute
  handling and ensure Person equality logic remains valid.

Result:
* EditCommand can now modify attributes as part of edit operations.
* Person model and related tests fully reflect the new attribute system.
